1
00:00:00,031 --> 00:00:03,152
[SPEAKER_03]: Hello, and welcome to this special meeting of the Medford Zoning Board of Appeals.

2
00:00:03,392 --> 00:00:06,013
[SPEAKER_03]: We're going to take a quick recall and then we'll get started.

3
00:00:07,814 --> 00:00:08,534
[SPEAKER_03]: Jim Tirani?

4
00:00:09,454 --> 00:00:09,834
[SPEAKER_03]: Present.

5
00:00:10,835 --> 00:00:11,575
[SPEAKER_03]: Yvette Velez?

6
00:00:12,215 --> 00:00:12,635
[SPEAKER_06]: Present.

7
00:00:13,656 --> 00:00:14,256
[SPEAKER_03]: Andre LaRue?

8
00:00:15,036 --> 00:00:15,476
[SPEAKER_03]: Present.

9
00:00:16,077 --> 00:00:16,897
[SPEAKER_03]: Jamie Thompson?

10
00:00:17,717 --> 00:00:18,017
[SPEAKER_03]: Present.

11
00:00:19,018 --> 00:00:19,698
[SPEAKER_03]: Mike Caldera?

12
00:00:19,758 --> 00:00:20,178
[SPEAKER_03]: Present.

13
00:00:20,818 --> 00:00:21,879
[SPEAKER_03]: All right, we have a quorum.

14
00:00:21,959 --> 00:00:23,139
[SPEAKER_03]: Dennis, can you please kick us off?

15
00:00:26,236 --> 00:00:36,745
[SPEAKER_00]: On March 29, 2023, Governor Healey signed into law a Supplemental Budget Bill, which, among other things, extends the temporary provisions pertaining to the Open Meeting Law to March 31, 2025.

16
00:00:37,025 --> 00:00:47,974
[SPEAKER_00]: Typically, this further extension allows public bodies to hold meetings without a quorum of the public body physically present at a meeting location and provide adequate alternative access to remote meetings.

17
00:00:49,776 --> 00:00:54,560
[SPEAKER_00]: The language does not make any substantive changes to the Open Meeting Law other than extending the expiration date of the temporary provisions

18
00:00:55,005 --> 00:00:58,047
[SPEAKER_00]: regarding remote meetings from March 31st, 2023 to March 31st, 2025.

19
00:00:58,107 --> 00:01:06,434
[SPEAKER_12]: Thank you, Dennis, and can you read the first matter, please?

20
00:01:06,454 --> 00:01:12,138
[SPEAKER_00]: 4000 Mystic Valley Parkway, case number 40B-2022-01, continued from June 5th, 2023.

21
00:01:13,199 --> 00:01:22,887
[SPEAKER_00]: The resumption of consideration of the petition of MVP Mystic LLC, an affiliate of Mill Creek Residential Trust LLC, for a comprehensive permit pursuant to Massachusetts General Laws Chapter 40B,

22
00:01:23,771 --> 00:01:33,115
[SPEAKER_00]: for multifamily eight-story apartment development consisting of two buildings located in approximately three acres of land at 4000 parkway, property ID 7-02-10.

23
00:01:33,995 --> 00:01:45,960
[SPEAKER_00]: This proposal will be developed as an approximately 350-unit rental apartment building containing a mixed studio, one, two, and three-bedroom apartments, with 25% of the total units being designated as affordable housing to low- or moderate-income households.

24
00:01:48,051 --> 00:01:49,052
[SPEAKER_03]: Great, thank you, Dennis.

25
00:01:49,652 --> 00:01:53,674
[SPEAKER_03]: Alright folks, so this is a long running hearing.

26
00:01:54,834 --> 00:01:59,237
[SPEAKER_03]: We have had a number of sessions before this where we've

27
00:02:00,339 --> 00:02:13,710
[SPEAKER_03]: had a chance to talk through several versions of the plan packet, to consider peer review feedback, and to provide comments.

28
00:02:13,790 --> 00:02:19,996
[SPEAKER_03]: And then iteratively, the board and the applicant have made progress to today's date.

29
00:02:20,116 --> 00:02:22,278
[SPEAKER_03]: And so at our last hearing,

30
00:02:24,234 --> 00:02:32,224
[SPEAKER_03]: There was a draft of some conditions circulated that no one really had enough time to read in advance.

31
00:02:33,005 --> 00:02:39,152
[SPEAKER_03]: The primary topic for today's meeting is to now that the.

32
00:02:39,873 --> 00:02:50,736
[SPEAKER_03]: applicant has had some additional time to review those draft conditions, to talk through any elements they'd like to discuss and any call outs they'd like to make.

33
00:02:52,156 --> 00:02:58,838
[SPEAKER_03]: Additionally, there were some ongoing discussions between the applicant and the city regarding linkage credits.

34
00:02:59,638 --> 00:03:02,619
[SPEAKER_03]: And so we can check in to see if there's any updates on that.

35
00:03:04,259 --> 00:03:09,603
[SPEAKER_03]: The intention, as stated last meeting, was to close the hearing tonight.

36
00:03:09,983 --> 00:03:11,825
[SPEAKER_03]: I've heard that the applicant may

37
00:03:12,893 --> 00:03:18,075
[SPEAKER_03]: to change that plan, so we can also talk through that at the appropriate time.

38
00:03:19,775 --> 00:03:21,216
[SPEAKER_03]: Yeah, so that's the plan for tonight.

39
00:03:21,236 --> 00:03:25,137
[SPEAKER_03]: I see you've got several representatives for the applicant.

40
00:03:25,417 --> 00:03:26,978
[SPEAKER_03]: We'll start with Mr. Alexander.

41
00:03:27,018 --> 00:03:33,580
[SPEAKER_03]: Mr. Alexander, is that the agenda you had in mind for tonight?

42
00:03:33,620 --> 00:03:36,981
[SPEAKER_03]: Is there anything else you'd like to discuss or change?

43
00:03:37,521 --> 00:03:40,262
[SPEAKER_15]: Yeah, good evening, Mr. Chair, members of the board.

