84
00:08:25,443 --> 00:08:33,590
[SPEAKER_14]: I think the decision, the draft conditions that have been provided maybe contemplated a project

85
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:41,285
[SPEAKER_14]: that hasn't benefited by the iterative peer review that we've worked on with Mr. Reardon and Mr. Bomer.

86
00:08:41,925 --> 00:08:48,370
[SPEAKER_14]: And so many of the comments that we had in here, and I'm not going to go through every comment.

87
00:08:48,590 --> 00:08:53,494
[SPEAKER_14]: We're happy to answer questions about specifics, but I think a better use of time is an overview.

88
00:08:53,534 --> 00:09:04,122
[SPEAKER_14]: But what we did was picking up on a comment that we talked about, and it might've been two hearings ago with Mr. Reardon, that given the iterative plan design and where we are with the current

89
00:09:04,759 --> 00:09:17,767
[SPEAKER_14]: May 12th set of plans, the appropriate next step would be to advance to the building permit plan set and not do another iteration of ZBA plans.

90
00:09:18,628 --> 00:09:29,354
[SPEAKER_14]: And the types of remaining comments that are out there in any comment letters or the normal types of refinements can be dealt with in a building permit plan set.

91
00:09:29,374 --> 00:09:33,617
[SPEAKER_14]: So that's many of the changes are to deal with and account for that.

92
00:09:35,429 --> 00:09:44,494
[SPEAKER_14]: Other changes in this decision, and again, I won't call all of them out, are to pick up some of the good work that we did through the peer review.

93
00:09:44,514 --> 00:10:01,383
[SPEAKER_14]: So, for example, the decision had a lot in there about a snow storage plan, a snow management plan, maybe contemplating a suburban type project site that would have a lot of roadways and snow storage areas.

94
00:10:01,423 --> 00:10:02,003
[SPEAKER_14]: We've committed.

95
00:10:03,012 --> 00:10:06,293
[SPEAKER_14]: previously that snow that falls will be removed in 24 hours.

96
00:10:06,513 --> 00:10:10,934
[SPEAKER_14]: So we've just simplified that condition and clarified that.

97
00:10:11,394 --> 00:10:17,436
[SPEAKER_14]: We've clarified as well that, you know, just some things that will happen on a timing basis.

98
00:10:18,496 --> 00:10:27,538
[SPEAKER_14]: For example, we will be able to provide with the building permit plan set a signage plan for the residential signage on the building.

99
00:10:28,292 --> 00:10:33,633
[SPEAKER_14]: We haven't spent a lot of time talking about residential signage, and this is not going to be a heavily signed project.

100
00:10:34,033 --> 00:10:48,396
[SPEAKER_14]: Mill Creek tends towards modest signage, but we will know enough about our signage to be able to present that at the time of the building permit plan set, and if necessary, request waivers for that.

101
00:10:49,576 --> 00:10:54,597
[SPEAKER_14]: But related to signage, we won't know, likely,

102
00:10:56,519 --> 00:11:00,521
[SPEAKER_14]: who our tenants are going to be in that ground floor retail space until in the future.

103
00:11:01,461 --> 00:11:04,723
[SPEAKER_14]: So what we try to do is split that signage into two buckets.

104
00:11:04,763 --> 00:11:10,526
[SPEAKER_14]: There's the residential signage, which we'll know about a building permit and the retail signage that may not be until later.

105
00:11:11,046 --> 00:11:17,069
[SPEAKER_14]: And then to the extent that doesn't, or would require a waiver, we would come back to the board for that.

106
00:11:19,650 --> 00:11:21,491
[SPEAKER_14]: Some other changes in here were,

107
00:11:26,618 --> 00:11:38,624
[SPEAKER_14]: I'm trying to just kind of refine a little bit some of the language about the phased occupancy and the phased certificates of occupancy that I know that Mill Creek had a great meeting with the building commissioner.

108
00:11:38,644 --> 00:11:42,606
[SPEAKER_14]: So some of those changes, we're just trying to be a little bit more specific.

109
