138
00:14:14,580 --> 00:14:26,792
[SPEAKER_15]: So an example is one of the comments from the peer reviewers was that a bike rack is blocking the path of a sidewalk.

139
00:14:29,026 --> 00:14:33,749
[SPEAKER_15]: southeast part of the project should probably be extended to have a continuous path.

140
00:14:34,370 --> 00:14:36,231
[SPEAKER_15]: And we think that's a good idea.

141
00:14:36,351 --> 00:14:37,712
[SPEAKER_15]: And we think that's a change we'll make.

142
00:14:38,172 --> 00:14:44,436
[SPEAKER_15]: But that will, you know, mildly or minorly change the calculations, for instance, on the landscape area.

143
00:14:44,957 --> 00:14:54,203
[SPEAKER_15]: And so making a change like that, then a change to the landscape area, as insignificant as it is, we just want to make sure that doesn't then require some other

144
00:14:58,259 --> 00:15:06,342
[SPEAKER_15]: sort of a de minimis change that is only being made because of compliance with the conditions set forth here.

145
00:15:08,082 --> 00:15:08,882
[SPEAKER_14]: Thanks, Sam.

146
00:15:08,943 --> 00:15:09,583
[SPEAKER_14]: Great example.

147
00:15:11,583 --> 00:15:26,008
[SPEAKER_14]: Here, just in the scale that I've got, you can't see my marginal comments, which I try to include just to illustrate is we simplified this text a little bit in that in a later condition, we will file copies of all permits with the building commissioner.

148
00:15:27,032 --> 00:15:36,339
[SPEAKER_14]: And we kept this language, which my recollection in blue had been provided by Mr. Forty, and so that's been kept unaltered in the decision.

149
00:15:38,340 --> 00:15:45,546
[SPEAKER_14]: Again, I don't want to go through all of these, but here, this is what I was talking about for snow storage.

150
00:15:49,422 --> 00:15:55,004
[SPEAKER_14]: where we just rather than talk about a snow storage management plan, we've just included the express conditions.

151
00:15:55,265 --> 00:15:59,506
[SPEAKER_14]: Snow shall not be stored anywhere on the interior access ways or wetland resource areas.

152
00:16:00,567 --> 00:16:03,828
[SPEAKER_14]: Snow accumulated must be removed from the site within 24 hours.

153
00:16:04,508 --> 00:16:09,811
[SPEAKER_14]: I think that's consistent with our conversations with the board and our peer review.

154
00:16:15,533 --> 00:16:17,094
[SPEAKER_14]: And some of these are just cleanup changes.

155
00:16:19,218 --> 00:16:31,682
