[SPEAKER_01]: with a 40 B because it's too broad.

341
00:36:45,178 --> 00:37:06,470
[SPEAKER_01]: Um, I think if the applicant put together a list of, you know, a wish list of all the things that they could possibly want in their building and possibly not want, um, you know, I think it would be, I think it would, it would be beneficial, um, not only to the city's interest, but for the perpetuity of the, of the order, because here again, you know, these projects sometimes get sold.

342
00:37:06,530 --> 00:37:07,851
[SPEAKER_01]: I'm not saying it's happening here.

343
00:37:08,351 --> 00:37:12,093
[SPEAKER_01]: But these projects can be sold and new owners have new ideas.

344
00:37:12,673 --> 00:37:21,218
[SPEAKER_01]: And we want to make sure that it's memorialized in stone, that there are limits to whatever commercial space is below on the ground level.

345
00:37:21,518 --> 00:37:29,102
[SPEAKER_01]: I just think it's prudent to at least have some parameters where these are the uses that are allowed.

346
00:37:31,617 --> 00:37:37,399
[SPEAKER_01]: No uses by special permit will be allowed without going through the permit granting authority that's appropriate.

347
00:37:37,499 --> 00:37:47,884
[SPEAKER_01]: And, you know, I think even with the signage, you know, there can be a certain amount of square foot signage that's allowed, you know, by right with the project, you know, provided that it meets all the requirements.

348
00:37:48,004 --> 00:37:56,587
[SPEAKER_01]: And so that's kind of what I'd like to see with this commercial tenant space, you know, that somehow is, you know, has some parameters.

349
00:37:59,923 --> 00:38:00,663
[SPEAKER_01]: Go ahead, please.

