00:38:29,792 --> 00:38:32,093
[SPEAKER_03]: before the special permit.

353
00:38:32,634 --> 00:38:39,337
[SPEAKER_03]: My understanding is the applicant would then, if that was the decision, would then have two avenues at their disposal.

354
00:38:39,358 --> 00:38:51,124
[SPEAKER_03]: They could, once the commercial use is identified, go through that process outside of the comprehensive permit process, or they could come back for that specific element.

355
00:38:51,184 --> 00:38:55,206
[SPEAKER_03]: So I just wanted to check in with the applicant if,

356
00:38:57,103 --> 00:39:16,109
[SPEAKER_03]: you would have concerns with language, just asserting that essentially, like based on what we know right now, this commercial use is expected to either be a by right use within a district or one of,

357
00:39:17,629 --> 00:39:28,073
[SPEAKER_03]: explicitly listed set of uses that are not allowed within the district that we know might be good candidates.

358
00:39:28,554 --> 00:39:38,718
[SPEAKER_03]: And everything else would just be, there would be language asserting that, hey, this does require you to go before the SPGA and then

359
00:39:39,782 --> 00:39:52,029
[SPEAKER_03]: at the relevant time when you have a tenant in mind, you would then make a call, okay, do I go before the SPGA or do I go back before the Zoning Board of Appeals with an update of the comprehensive permit?

360
00:39:52,049 --> 00:39:55,151
[SPEAKER_03]: So I just wanted to check in with you for your thoughts on that.

361
00:39:55,911 --> 00:39:56,952
[SPEAKER_14]: Yeah, thank you.

362
