367
00:40:27,315 --> 00:40:30,278
[SPEAKER_14]: So we agreed to include that in the project.

368
00:40:30,338 --> 00:40:34,802
[SPEAKER_14]: So I think that's an important piece of context here.

369
00:40:35,803 --> 00:40:43,889
[SPEAKER_14]: Two, in a 40B, there can be some incidental retail, but that doesn't send us to a community development board or other permit granting authority.

370
00:40:43,969 --> 00:40:45,470
[SPEAKER_14]: Everything is done in the comp permit.

371
00:40:46,631 --> 00:40:53,496
[SPEAKER_14]: What we had done in our original waiver list, and it's on page two of the waiver list, where we intentionally stayed a bit broad.

372
00:40:53,776 --> 00:40:57,939
[SPEAKER_14]: We had been asked by the city to put some ground floor retail on the project.

373
00:40:58,580 --> 00:41:04,004
[SPEAKER_14]: So we included a broad waiver allowing retail uses

374
00:41:04,969 --> 00:41:08,410
[SPEAKER_14]: And we called it commercial slash retail.

