383
00:41:43,574 --> 00:41:53,797
[SPEAKER_14]: And in order to be flexible, in order to be nimble in talking to tenants for the small space, we need to have some buckets of uses that we can have allowed.

384
00:41:53,857 --> 00:41:58,799
[SPEAKER_14]: So what we could do, I think, is we could talk about a waiver to allow

385
00:41:59,678 --> 00:42:01,659
[SPEAKER_14]: Retail sales, that's in use.

386
00:42:03,801 --> 00:42:06,862
[SPEAKER_14]: Convenience retail, neighborhood retail.

387
00:42:08,924 --> 00:42:17,169
[SPEAKER_14]: I don't know, Alicia, what a commercial service establishment is, if that's like a yoga store, not store, yoga studio.

388
00:42:19,230 --> 00:42:25,554
[SPEAKER_14]: And then we could talk about an eating place without a drive-thru, because our project isn't set up for a drive-thru, so we don't need a drive-thru.

389
00:42:25,574 --> 00:42:28,996
[SPEAKER_14]: But if a coffee shop is an eating place without a drive-thru, then yes,

390
00:42:29,704 --> 00:42:37,808
[SPEAKER_14]: So I think with a relatively light pen, we could add four similar uses to retail to our waiver list.

391
00:42:38,589 --> 00:42:41,770
[SPEAKER_14]: Right now we've got retail, which is the retail sales are here.

392
00:42:42,271 --> 00:42:46,573
[SPEAKER_14]: We could do convenience retail, neighborhood retail.

393
00:42:47,493 --> 00:42:50,875
[SPEAKER_14]: I could look at the definitions to what a consumer service establishment is.

394
00:42:51,555 --> 00:42:54,237
[SPEAKER_14]: And then I think we should do meeting place without drive-through.

395
00:42:54,957 --> 00:42:58,299
[SPEAKER_14]: I think that's the way to deal with this, to give the applicant the ability

396
00:42:58,922 --> 00:43:02,383
[SPEAKER_14]: to lease up, but also keep a relatively restricted use.

397
00:43:02,443 --> 00:43:10,225
[SPEAKER_14]: In that case, for example, we haven't listed a motor vehicle light service station as something that's being waived.

398
00:43:10,245 --> 00:43:11,706
[SPEAKER_14]: So that can't be a use, right?

399
00:43:11,766 --> 00:43:19,828
[SPEAKER_14]: So it's only the stuff that we've listed and we're not trying to do a drive-through, we're not trying to do a marijuana establishment, we're not trying to do a body art establishment.

400
00:43:19,848 --> 00:43:23,389
[SPEAKER_14]: I think that's probably a good way of moving forward.

401
00:43:24,292 --> 00:43:29,946
[SPEAKER_15]: Yeah, Chris, if I, if I might, I think that this is a great discussion to have.

402
00:43:29,966 --> 00:43:31,770
[SPEAKER_15]: I appreciate the building commissioner bringing it up.

403
00:43:31,810 --> 00:43:32,712
[SPEAKER_15]: But the good news is.

404
