[SPEAKER_03]: What I'm hearing is that the applicants agreeable to review the use table and just list off everything that you consider that you want to be able to market this for.

431
00:46:14,945 --> 00:46:22,747
[SPEAKER_03]: And then I think the board also wants you to have that flexibility to find it

432
00:46:26,159 --> 00:46:27,920
[SPEAKER_03]: find a renter for that space.

433
00:46:27,980 --> 00:46:33,702
[SPEAKER_03]: So yeah, the only thing I'll call out, I guess there is a slight downside to this.

434
00:46:33,882 --> 00:46:36,363
[SPEAKER_03]: I mean, I think it's the right way to go.

435
00:46:37,224 --> 00:46:46,387
[SPEAKER_03]: So the downside would be if the use table changes, if new uses are introduced, then suddenly there's a restriction that maybe doesn't need to be there.

436
00:46:46,447 --> 00:46:54,151
[SPEAKER_03]: But then on the flip side, if uses are added and we use language in the negative rather than the positive,

437
00:46:55,091 --> 00:46:56,092
[SPEAKER_03]: creates a bunch of loopholes.

438
00:46:56,112 --> 00:47:11,485
[SPEAKER_03]: So I think the best strategy is just go with a broad but credible list of uses that you want to market this commercial space for, and then the board will review that list at the appropriate time.

439
00:47:11,545 --> 00:47:17,490
[SPEAKER_03]: And if for some reason we take issue with particular uses, we can discuss that.

