[SPEAKER_03]: I don't really know where we are in the drafting process, but yes, I think it would be fair to characterize it as this process has converged.

1358
02:32:47,206 --> 02:32:49,848
[SPEAKER_03]: So I think we're largely aligned.

1359
02:32:50,328 --> 02:32:59,234
[SPEAKER_03]: The board hasn't really deliberated on all the different elements, but I'd be willing to stipulate that there's nothing good that's going to be like a wild change last minute.

1360
02:32:59,615 --> 02:33:06,239
[SPEAKER_08]: So the pieces that are left to draft are the procedural history, the governing law,

1361
02:33:07,240 --> 02:33:12,586
[SPEAKER_08]: The jurisdictional findings and the factual findings and then of course packaging up whatever the exhibits are.

1362
02:33:14,228 --> 02:33:17,051
[SPEAKER_08]: The jurisdictional findings are not difficult to write.

1363
02:33:19,106 --> 02:33:23,408
[SPEAKER_08]: I don't really get the sense from what I've seen that the factual findings are particularly difficult to write.

1364
02:33:23,448 --> 02:33:35,012
[SPEAKER_08]: I think the procedural history in this case is probably a little different from some decisions I've written just because of the romance situation, but I don't see this as a, I don't know, you're all being very quiet.

1365
02:33:35,112 --> 02:33:43,935
[SPEAKER_08]: So somebody push back if you disagree, but I don't know why we can't get this decision done well in advance of a July 11th meeting.

1366
02:33:48,037 --> 02:33:48,677
[SPEAKER_14]: I agree.

1367
02:33:49,119 --> 02:33:52,122
[SPEAKER_14]: I mean, I think we're very close.

1368
02:33:52,642 --> 02:33:59,269
[SPEAKER_14]: I heard the board say that, you know, they have what they need from us and others in respect of the linkage waiver.

1369
02:34:02,071 --> 02:34:14,023
[SPEAKER_14]: You know, I think we could, with a short recess, you know, likely send to the night, to tonight even, you know, a quickly updated

1370
02:34:15,053 --> 02:34:18,935
[SPEAKER_14]: list and the waivers to add those other uses.

1371
02:34:19,735 --> 02:34:27,259
[SPEAKER_14]: And then I could forward tonight while the hearings open, the decision that I was marking up as we went along here.

1372
02:34:27,279 --> 02:34:31,782
[SPEAKER_14]: And conceivably we could even have the board close tonight.

1373
02:34:32,582 --> 02:34:41,867
[SPEAKER_14]: And then when we come back on the 11th, it's the board, you know, really looking at the other aspects of the decision that you and Amy will work on.

1374
02:34:42,499 --> 02:34:46,082
[SPEAKER_14]: procedural findings, jurisdictional findings, things of that nature.

1375
02:34:46,122 --> 02:34:58,372
[SPEAKER_14]: But it seems to me, I'm interested in the board's reaction, but it seems to me that we've had a very fulsome discussion of conditions and people had an opportunity to ask questions.

1376
02:34:58,412 --> 02:35:07,900
[SPEAKER_14]: So I think we're very close and a large part of me, and I'm glad we had the opportunity of tonight because I came in at night not knowing how much we would have a chance to cover.

1377
02:35:07,920 --> 02:35:09,921
[SPEAKER_14]: I think we've covered a great breadth of ground.

1378
02:35:11,480 --> 02:35:12,420
[SPEAKER_14]: I need to talk to Tim.

1379
02:35:12,460 --> 02:35:18,702
[SPEAKER_14]: And again, if we were at a hearing table, he might be kicking me, but we might be able to close this tonight.

1380
02:35:19,022 --> 02:35:29,485
[SPEAKER_14]: And in which case, the 11th, if that's the next meeting that people get together, that could be a quick meeting where the board is reviewing your decision, Judy, and voting it.

1381
02:35:29,925 --> 02:35:30,085
[SPEAKER_08]: Yeah.

1382
02:35:30,205 --> 02:35:31,906
[SPEAKER_08]: I mean, the last thing I want to do is drag this out.

1383
02:35:32,106 --> 02:35:33,987
[SPEAKER_08]: And I really am not trying to be difficult.

1384
02:35:34,047 --> 02:35:36,107
[SPEAKER_08]: I'm just trying to preserve protocol here.

1385
02:35:36,207 --> 02:35:38,788
[SPEAKER_08]: And I don't think if the hearing

1386
02:35:39,644 --> 02:35:47,029
[SPEAKER_08]: were closed tonight, then I would have to advise the board not to take any additional information because the closing of the hearing means they have what they need.

1387
02:35:48,089 --> 02:35:55,073
[SPEAKER_08]: So if there's some way miraculously to cure this this evening, I think that's great.

1388
02:35:55,474 --> 02:36:02,398
[SPEAKER_08]: I mean, I can tell you, I'm not gonna stay on much longer, but I mean, if you think you can somehow do this, that's totally up to you.

1389
02:36:02,478 --> 02:36:05,520
[SPEAKER_08]: I'm not wanting to drag this out, believe me, for any of you.

1390
02:36:07,063 --> 02:36:07,724
[SPEAKER_08]: Really, I don't.

1391
02:36:07,804 --> 02:36:12,888
[SPEAKER_08]: I mean, everybody's been through so much on this case that... We're very close.

1392
02:36:12,988 --> 02:36:14,329
[SPEAKER_14]: We're very... I know.

1393
02:36:14,889 --> 02:36:29,901
[SPEAKER_14]: Tim, do you want to... If we could ask the board's indulgence, if Tim and I and Louise could shut our cameras and microphones off for maybe five minutes, and we take a five-minute recess, and then we reconvene.

1394
02:36:30,662 --> 02:36:34,645
[SPEAKER_14]: I know the hour is late, but we're so close that with a quick conversation with Tim and then

1395
02:36:35,322 --> 02:36:37,724
[SPEAKER_14]: potentially we could even get these materials back to you this evening.

1396
02:36:39,705 --> 02:36:40,806
[SPEAKER_03]: Tim, what are your thoughts?

1397
