[SPEAKER_15]: That was very helpful.

1479
02:44:00,260 --> 02:44:01,661
[SPEAKER_15]: Hopefully it was on your side as well.

1480
02:44:01,941 --> 02:44:10,986
[SPEAKER_15]: I think, you know, without getting into too much detail, I think the applicant and our team is in agreement with Ms.

1481
02:44:11,026 --> 02:44:11,986
[SPEAKER_15]: Barrett, right?

1482
02:44:12,466 --> 02:44:15,688
[SPEAKER_15]: The board has gathered the information they need.

1483
02:44:15,868 --> 02:44:22,532
We've gone through in detail tonight the draft conditions with revisions as proposed.

1484
02:44:23,298 --> 02:44:25,879
[SPEAKER_15]: It feels like there is generally a meeting of the minds.

1485
02:44:26,979 --> 02:44:38,404
[SPEAKER_15]: And our thought is that we can, as we talked about just before the recess, we can send now the minor changes to the draft conditions that we reviewed tonight.

1486
02:44:38,904 --> 02:44:48,027
[SPEAKER_15]: We can send now bracketed revisions to the waiver lists to make sure that gets cleaned up to include the appropriate commercial uses.

1487
02:44:50,789 --> 02:45:01,517
[SPEAKER_15]: you know, if we were talking about a week or a few days of extending the hearing to make sure that these changes were incorporated, I think that might make sense.

1488
02:45:01,577 --> 02:45:09,883
[SPEAKER_15]: But understanding the board's schedule and that would be, you know, four to five weeks, it doesn't feel like that's an appropriate sort of give and take.

1489
02:45:11,043 --> 02:45:12,905
[SPEAKER_15]: So I think, you know, where we're coming out,

1490
02:45:13,770 --> 02:45:26,794
[SPEAKER_15]: is that we're in agreement on getting these final items to the board now, close the hearing tonight, and the board's schedule will be what it will be on issuing the final permit and all the documentation.

1491
02:45:29,034 --> 02:45:30,995
[SPEAKER_03]: All right, well thank you for that update.

1492
02:45:31,015 --> 02:45:34,416
[SPEAKER_03]: So then here's what I propose.

1493
02:45:34,456 --> 02:45:37,817
[SPEAKER_03]: So why don't, if you have things you want to send off,

1494
02:45:38,765 --> 02:45:41,148
[SPEAKER_03]: feel free to send those at any point while I'm talking.

1495
02:45:42,410 --> 02:45:56,548
[SPEAKER_03]: And then, so I do just want to, since the intention is to close tonight, I don't see a member of the public on the call anymore, but I do just want to,

1496
02:45:58,268 --> 02:46:03,969
[SPEAKER_03]: open once more for public comment in case there's any last comments before we close.

1497
02:46:04,469 --> 02:46:05,870
[SPEAKER_03]: So we can do that in a moment.

1498
02:46:05,930 --> 02:46:14,831
[SPEAKER_03]: And then Judy procedurally, we would just vote on closure.

1499
02:46:14,851 --> 02:46:18,732
[SPEAKER_03]: So we would just vote to close the hearing and that's it.

1500
02:46:18,852 --> 02:46:20,672
[SPEAKER_03]: Or would it be to close an open delivery?

1501
02:46:20,713 --> 02:46:22,833
[SPEAKER_03]: Like we don't have to continue or anything.

1502
02:46:24,333 --> 02:46:34,318
[SPEAKER_03]: We just close the hearing, and then we separately will schedule for the 11th a special meeting to vote on findings and review the draft.

1503
02:46:34,338 --> 02:46:35,218
[SPEAKER_03]: You vote the decision.

1504
02:46:36,099 --> 02:46:37,659
[SPEAKER_03]: Yeah, the decision, right.

1505
02:46:37,919 --> 02:46:39,500
[SPEAKER_08]: Yeah, I mean, that's all you need to do.

1506
02:46:39,540 --> 02:46:43,822
[SPEAKER_08]: You vote to close the hearing, and then your next meeting is a meeting, not a hearing.

1507
02:46:44,723 --> 02:46:45,223
[SPEAKER_08]: Yeah, I see.

1508
02:46:45,423 --> 02:46:47,084
[SPEAKER_08]: And at that meeting, you would have

1509
02:46:48,006 --> 02:46:55,568
[SPEAKER_08]: the proposed final draft of the decision and the board can certainly look at it and ask for some changes if you want.

1510
02:46:55,588 --> 02:46:57,068
[SPEAKER_08]: There's nothing that says you can't.

1511
02:46:58,288 --> 02:47:06,150
[SPEAKER_08]: But I think what you wanna do by the end of that night is either bless the decision as written or agree on whatever tweaks you want.

1512
02:47:06,890 --> 02:47:14,172
[SPEAKER_08]: And then the board should authorize the chair to sign the decision and Amy or I will clean it up and get it to you.

1513
02:47:15,112 --> 02:47:16,253
[SPEAKER_03]: Great, okay.

1514
02:47:18,654 --> 02:47:25,139
[SPEAKER_03]: Wonderful, so then in that case, so chair awaits a motion to open public comment.

1515
02:47:29,922 --> 02:47:30,122
[SPEAKER_03]: So moved.

1516
02:47:30,202 --> 02:47:32,264
[SPEAKER_03]: Is there a second?

1517
02:47:34,205 --> 02:47:34,545
[SPEAKER_05]: Second.

1518
02:47:35,626 --> 02:47:38,428
[SPEAKER_03]: All right, we'll take a roll call of that.

1519
